channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: BREAKING: Now It's Jack Smith Who Wants to Silence Trump—Files Friday Night Gag Order Request
Louisiana classifies abortion drugs as controlled, dangerous substances after Gov. Landry greenlights proposal
item.description: Republican Louisiana Gov. Jeff Landry on Friday signed into law a proposal to classify mifepristone and misoprostol as controlled and dangerous substances.

item.title: Farm Bill Amendment Threatens Cannabis Industry
item.description: An amendment added to the House's version of the Farm Bill could end America's "brief experiment" with cannabis, essentially collapsing a $28 billion industry, The Hill reported.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: Kelvin Ellis Gives His Last Dollar to a Homeless Man, Who Happened to Be a Millionaire
Hunter Biden lawyers question who filled out form at center of gun trial set for June 3
item.description: Hunter Biden’s defense attorney signaled a key element of his defense strategy in a Delaware federal court on Friday: who exactly filled out the key federal gun form in question?

item.title: Sen. Cotton Makes Top 5 List for Trump VP Pick
item.description: Sen. Tom Cotton, R-Ark., has emerged as a top-five pick on the shortlist of Donald Trump's vice presidential candidates, The New York Times reported Friday.

item.title: Oh No, You Didn't! Jasmine Crockett Now Claims She Misspelled Her Name on Purpose
Colorado Gov. Polis signs funeral home regulatory crackdowns into law
item.description: Democratic Colorado Gov. Jared Polis on Friday signed off on two bills aimed at overhauling the state's notoriously lax oversight of the funeral home industry.

item.title: Gold Star Dad to Newsmax: Biden's Disrespect Needs to Stop
item.description: Coming up on the three-year anniversary of the Afghanistan suicide bombing that killed his son, gold star father Darin Hoover told Newsmax on Friday that he still has not heard from President Joe Biden or the administration, saying the disrespect "needs to stop."

item.title: WATCH: They Just Dropped the Official Trailer for the Sequel to '80s Classic 'Beetlejuice'
WV Gov. Justice ends jail staffing state of emergency after nearly 2 years
item.description: Republican West Virginia Gov. Jim Justice announced Friday his intent to end the state of emergency over staffing in the Mountain State's Department of Corrections.

item.title: Carrie Severino to Newsmax: Dems' Targeting of Alito 'Ludicrous'
item.description: The Democrats' efforts to construe Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito as an unhinged radical for flying a Revolutionary War-era flag outside his vacation home and that the flag is somehow connected to the events of Jan. 6, 2021, is "ludicrous," Carrie Severino told Newsmax.

item.title: HEARTBREAKING: Christian Missionary Couple From Missouri Murdered in Gang Attack in Haiti
Billionaire CEO Schwarzman changes course and backs Trump citing rising antisemitism as top concern
item.description: Billionaire Steve Schwarzman announced he will be supporting former President Donald Trump after previously calling for the GOP to move on to fresh leadership.

item.title: Chicago Officials Concerned About Violence at DNC Convention
item.description: Officials in Chicago are concerned about potential violence at the upcoming Democratic National Convention despite spending $75 million in taxpayer-funded money for security, reports the Daily Caller.
